== <Big><div style="text-shadow: 0 0 0.2em grey, 0 0.1em 0.05em grey, 0 -0.1em 0.05em grey, 0.05em 0 0.05em grey, -0.05em 0 0.05em grey;padding: 15px;font-family: Montagu Slab, Serif;text-align: center;font-size: 30px">Description</span></big> ==
{{Underline|aaaaaa}}
<Div style="border-left: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;border-right: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);">
{{Simple Image Block|image=Beach Town Level 135.1.png|caption=This is the first ever and the most known image of the sublevel, taken by a wanderer to report a new sublevel to the [[M.E.G.]]}}
[[Level 135.1]], also known as ''"Beach Town,"'' is a sublevel of [[Level 135]], which resembles its parent level’s dark, and infinite shoreline but exhibits a more structured and urbanized environment. The terrain consists of wet, and compact sand that glistens subtly under dim ambient lighting. Unlike the main level, [[Level 135.1]] contains narrow concrete pathways that can extend into the distance, bordered by malfunctioning streetlights that flicker intermittently or be completely dark. These paths provide the only stable walking surfaces amid the otherwise soft and unstable terrain.

Scattered across the landscape are modern residential houses, some appear pristine and other ones show signs of weathering and partial collapse. Certain areas host small shopping complexes or malls, their glass entrances are clouded with condensation and their interiors are subtly illuminated by failing emergency lights. Rare concrete blocks of various sizes are embedded in the sand, and have no apparent purpose but contribute to the half-finished feeling of the level.

Quicksand hazards are present but are significantly reduced compared to [[Level 135]], usually appearing in small patches measuring only 15–45 square centimeters. These are usually easy to step over but can still pose a danger if not carefully avoided.

The most distinctive anomaly in this sublevel is the occasional appearance of floating bubbles. These bubbles are rare and move silently through the air, and their surfaces reflect subtle light despite the lack of a clear source. They are ephemeral and burst without sound upon contact and leave no residue behind.

Visibility within [[Level 135.1]] behaves in an unstable and subtle manner, similar to its parent level but with a faint urban influence. The light provided by the flickering streetlights and dim glow from distant structures creates a false sense of security; beyond their limited range, the surroundings dissolve into a hazy darkness where shapes blur and distances become uncertain. Occasionally, visibility expands unnaturally, allows one to see several dozen meters ahead, and collapses moments later into a narrow range of clarity barely spanning a few feet. This changing illumination does not follow any logical pattern, and backtracking rarely restores a previously clear view. In moments of near-total obscurity, the faint reflection of bubbles or the dim silhouettes of structures may briefly emerge, which heighten the illusion of depth before vanishing once more.

Adding to the disquieting atmosphere, ambient sounds of waves crashing against an unseen shoreline and distant thunderstorms can occasionally be heard. The direction of these sounds is impossible to determine, and they persist even when no water or storm clouds are visible, which suggests an unknown or illusory origin.
</div>
