== <Big><div style="text-shadow: 0 0 0.2em grey, 0 0.1em 0.05em grey, 0 -0.1em 0.05em grey, 0.05em 0 0.05em grey, -0.05em 0 0.05em grey;padding: 15px;font-family: Montagu Slab, Serif;text-align: center;font-size: 20px">Cubinold Fungus // Fungus Tree</span></big> ==
{{Underline|5555}}
<Div style="border-left: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;border-right: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);">
{{Simple Image Block|image=Beach Town Level 135.1 2.png|caption=The well-known photograph of Cubinold Fungus in the growing age. Photographer is unknown.|align=left}}
The '''Cubinold Fungus''', also known as the ''Fungus Tree,'' is an entity within [[Level 135.1]]. It begins as a small fungal sprout within the sand, then develops into a thick, and trunk-like growth that resembles a combination of plant and fungus. Its surface ranges in color from rusty brown to a deep, and almost black color, and the texture changes between woody bark and damp mycelium. As it grows, the entity develops long, and flexible branches which extend outward in irregular patterns. These branches are not passive; they appear to reach for debris, fallen matter, or anything that stays near it.

The most unusual feature of the '''Cubinold Fungus''' is the beating cube that exists at the top of its central log. This cube aligns a rhythm, which resembles a heartbeat, and is widely believed to function as the entity’s core or heart. When destroyed, the '''Fungus Tree''' rapidly withers, and collapses into dust and brittle fragments. The cube itself seems vital to the organism’s survival, but it also plays a role in reproduction.

Once the '''Cubinold Fungus''' reaches its full height, roughly comparable to a pine tree, it begins to move slowly across the sandy terrain. Its branches sweep outward as it drags itself in uneven motions, and leaves shallow grooves in the ground. During this stage, smaller cubes occasionally start to grow along its limbs/branches. These cubes eventually fall to the ground, and if they remain intact, they can germinate into entirely new '''Fungus Trees'''. Cubes that fall from higher branches frequently shatter on impact, which leaves only inert fragments that never develop/grow further.

The lifespan of a '''Cubinold Fungus''' is inconsistent, and lasts anywhere from one year to over fourteen. In its final stage, the organism gradually weakens, its branches lose strength as the pulsating cube dims over. Over time, the entire structure collapses, and leaves behind only a hollowed log and the remains of its cubes. The sight of such remnants is common in certain areas of [[Level 135.1]], which serves as a reminder of both the presence and the eventual decay of these strange beings.
</div></div>
