== <Big><div style="text-shadow: 0 0 0.2em grey, 0 0.1em 0.05em grey, 0 -0.1em 0.05em grey, 0.05em 0 0.05em grey, -0.05em 0 0.05em grey;padding: 15px;font-family: Montagu Slab, Serif;text-align: center;font-size: 30px">Addendum</span></big> ==
{{Underline|aaaaaa}}
<Div style="border-left: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);padding: 15px;border-right: 1px solid var(--theme-border-color);">
<div class="featurebox" style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFFFFF 24px, #266C91 1px);background-size:40px 25px;border-radius: 0px; margin: 1em;font-family: Shadows Into Light Two;color: black">
<big>'''DAY 1'''</big><br>
''I don’t know how I got here. One moment I was on the shoreline, knee-deep in sand, the next I was walking on a concrete path that stretched further than I could see. There are houses here. Actual houses. Some look brand new, others look like they’ve been left to rot for decades. I found one with a mattress that wasn’t soaked through, so I’ll be staying there tonight. The lights outside flicker on and off. I can’t tell if it’s comforting or threatening.''

<Big>'''DAY ''3'''''</Big><br>
''The sounds won’t stop. Waves crashing, thunder rolling, and the horizon is empty and black. I walked toward the noise for hours, and the further I went, the darker it became until I couldn’t even see my hand in front of my face. When the lights flickered again, I was back near the houses, like I’d been walking in circles. <Span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">There are bubbles in the air sometimes. They float past me like soap, but when I try to touch them, thwy pop. I don’t know if I’m hallucanating or not.</span>''

<Big>'''DAY 5'''</big><br>
''<span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">I tried to explore a shopping mall. The glass doors were fogged, though the air is dry and heavy. Inside, emergency lights buzzed faintIy. I thought I saw a figure moving at the end of an aisle, but when the lights flickered, it was gone. The air smelled like mold, even though nothing looked rotten. I didn’t stay long. Something about the silence there fekt wrpng, like it was waiting for me to do somethinf.</span>''

<Big>'''<span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">Day… ''7''(I thinL)</span>'''</big><br>
''Found <span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">a tree, or maybe a fungus. It was growing taller than me, its branches are moving toward the sand like it was searching. At the top was a cube, it pulses like</span><span style="font-family: Rock Salt;"> a slow heartbeat. I stood and watched it for a while, until I realized its branches had inched closer, almost brush the ground near my feet. I ran before it could reach me. I can’t get the image out of my head. That cube… I swear it was watching me.</span>''

<Big>'''DAY <span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">''ma''ybe 9</span> <span style="font-family: Rock Salt;">or 10</span>'''</big><br>
''<span style="font-family: Rock Salt;">The liqhts ouIside my hause don’t flicker the same way anymore. They feel… delrberate. One blinks, then another. I wrate dovvn the pattern, and it l00ks like some kind of code. Mqybe there’s meaning here. Or maybe I’m losing my mind. Sometimes I think I hear voices in the thunder, too distant to make out but too real to ignore. I don’t know how long I’ve actually been here. —~<span>''

<big>'''<span style="font-family: Rock Salt;">Not Sure a''bout'' ''TH''E ''Cou''NT Anymore……</span>'''</big><br>
''<span style="font-family: Rock Salt;">I haven’t seen anyone else. No people. Just shadows, shapes moving at the edge of vIsIOn. I called Out onCa, and something answered, but the voice was wrong like it echoed from unqer the sand. I don’t call out anymore. Food is running low. I’ll have to risk searching again F0marrow… · or whatever “fomorrow” even means here.</span>''

<Div style="font-family: Rock Salt;">
<Big>'''???'''</big><br>
''The cubes are falling now. I saw one crash into the sand, shattered like glass. Another landed softly and began to grow, sprouting a pale log within hours. Soon there will be more of them, moving slowly through the dark. I don’t know how many there already are.''

''The lights are gone. Everything is gone. Only the cubes glow faintly, like eyes in the dark. I can hear the branches scraping, dragging, reaching. The thunder is louder now, close. I don’t think I’ll find my way Out. If anyone finds this, don’t follow the lights. Don’t trust the bubbles. Don’t stop moving. I think I'm G0Linh CraZV''
</Div>
</Div>
It is widely believed that the anonymous writer of this journal succumbed to the environmental toll of [[Level 135.1]] shortly after completing the final entry. Prolonged isolation, malnutrition, and constant exposure to anomalies, such as the flickering lights and the '''Fungus Trees''', appear to have broken down his physical and psychological stability, and may had turn the author into the after effects of the [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]].
</div>
